SUMMARY:Downtown Evanston Chocolate Crawl
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260212T163000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260212T193000
UID:c4ce7746e491104ca7137cc80f6ab250@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Downtown Evanston in celebrating the season of love at th
 eir Love Local Chocolate Crawl on Thursday\, February 12\, from 4:30 p.m. 
 to 7:30 p.m. Bundle up and gather your friends\, coworkers and family (yes
 \, this is kid-friendly!) for an evening stroll stopping in local shops to
  enjoy a variety of chocolate treats and special offers. Find the perfect 
 gifts for your loved ones or perhaps a little something special for yourse
 lf! <a rel="noopener" href="https://downtownevanston.org/valentinesday" ta
 rget="_blank">Check out the Valentine's specials</a>. This is a free event
  but\, <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://forms.gle/8jpaGf1CSryTv6
 ha6" target="_blank">please register</a>. <strong>After the crawl</strong>
 \, be sure to treat yourself and your Valentine to dinner and a sweet trea
 t in Downtown Evanston!
LOCATION:Evanston\, IL
URL:https://downtownevanston.org/lovelocalchocolatecrawl
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Downtown Evanston S'mores on the Square
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T170000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T190000
UID:e02bd5255db215f7d61fbe5777ad0ea4@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<p data-start="0" data-end="222">Downtown Evanston\, in partne
 rship with the City of Evanston Parks and Recreation Department\, will hos
 t the third annual <strong data-start="120" data-end="145">S&rsquo\;mores 
 on the Square</strong>\, a family-friendly winter gathering at Fountain Sq
 uare.&nbsp\;The free event will take place on Saturday\, March 7\, from 5 
 to 7 p.m.\, with a rain date of March 14\, and is open to residents and vi
 sitors of all ages. Attendees are invited to roast marshmallows and connec
 t with the community around outdoor fire pits.&nbsp\;<br /><br />Downtown 
 Evanston will provide complimentary s&rsquo\;mores kits (one per person)\,
  while Evanston Parks &amp\; Recreation will supply the fire pits. Partici
 pants may also bring additional s&rsquo\;mores ingredients. Visitors are e
 ncouraged to explore downtown Evanston before or after the event for dinin
 g and drinks</p>
LOCATION:Fountain Square
URL:https://downtownevanston.org/smoresonthesquare
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Downtown Evanston Earth Day CleanUp
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T120000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T140000
UID:102c23f0450f186bc0fea409f6dcb09c@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Downtown Evanston and&nbsp\;<a rel="noopener noreferrer" 
 href="https://www.wcofe.org/" target="_blank">The Woman's Club of Evanston
 </a> on Sunday\, April 26\, from noon to 2 p.m. for Downtown Evanston's an
 nual Earth Day Clean-Up<strong>&nbsp\;</strong>event aimed at fostering co
 mmunity engagement and environmental stewardship. Individuals\, families\,
  office groups\, students are all encouraged to lend a hand in making our 
 downtown business district a cleaner\, greener place to live\, work and vi
 sit!&nbsp\;<br /><br />Participants will gather at Fountain Square to get 
 outfitted with gloves\, bags and maps before heading out to pick-up litter
  and debris. When finished\, participants will bring the trash bags back t
 o Fountain Square for disposal.&nbsp\;
LOCATION:Downtown Evanston
URL:https://downtownevanston.org/annual-events
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
