BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Levy Lecture Series: 'Momma Kemba' Portrays Fannie Lou Hamer
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260205T143000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260205T160000
UID:b3d19db16e4e25a7bd095e6026c177ec@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-ric
 h-text__text">Join the Levy Senior Center Foundation on Thursday\, Februar
 y 5\, at 2:30 p.m.&nbsp\;for a special hybrid Levy Lecture in celebration 
 of Black History Month\, held in person&nbsp\;in Bobby&rsquo\;s Room&nbsp\
 ;at the Levy Senior Center and&nbsp\;online via Zoom.</span><span class="w
 ixui-rich-text__text">&#8203\;</span></p>\n<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-tex
 t__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">Acclaimed storyteller &lsquo\
 ;Momma Kemba&rsquo\; will present a fully costumed\, dramatic portrayal of
  iconic civil rights leader Fannie Lou Hamer\, bringing to life her powerf
 ul legacy as a voice for desegregation\, voting rights\, and economic secu
 rity for African Americans.</span><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">&#82
 03\;</span></p>\n<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixu
 i-rich-text__text">Gain a deeper insight into Fannie Lou Hamer&rsquo\;s en
 during impact on American history. This&nbsp\;hybrid&nbsp\;Levy Lecture is
 &nbsp\;free to attend\, but&nbsp\;registration is required.</span></p>
LOCATION:Levy Senior Center
URL:https://www.lscfevanston.org/levy-lecture-series
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kids First Aid Event
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260301T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260301T143000
UID:8f2ff1e39ab2a12f305659311fba1862@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<span class="header">Kids First Aid Event<br /></span><br />\n
 <p data-font="16">Calling All Young Heroes! Is your child ready to level u
 p their confidence and emergency readiness? The Evanston Fire Department i
 s hosting a Kids First Aid Event on Sunday\, March 1st! Sessions at 9 a.m.
 \, 11 a.m.\, and 1 p.m. Children will be split up by the following age gro
 ups: 1st/2nd grade\, 3rd/4th/5th grade\, and 6th/7th/8th grade.&nbsp\;<br 
 data-font="16" /><br data-font="16" />Your child will: Build their own fir
 st-aid kit\, Learn essential first-aid skills\, and master hands-only CPR 
 basics. Spaces fill up fast\, so sign up your future hero today! 1st throu
 gh 8th graders are welcome. The $20 fee covers the cost of supplies.&nbsp\
 ;<a rel="noopener" href="https://arts.formstack.com/forms/2026kidsfirstaid
 event" target="_blank" data-font="16">Register now</a>!&nbsp\;</p>
LOCATION:Levy Senior Center\, 300 Dodge Ave\, Evanston\, IL 60202
URL:https://arts.formstack.com/forms/2026kidsfirstaidevent
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Evanston Animal Shelter: The Love of Animals Art Show
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T120000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T170000
UID:58085c0f46d6ba63f54cd34660b1c242@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<div class="StructuredModuleRenderer_structuredContent__k7mNB 
 StructuredModuleRenderer_text__GaXOv" data-testid="text-content">\n<div>&n
 bsp\;</div>\n</div>\n<div class="StructuredModuleRenderer_structuredConten
 t__k7mNB StructuredModuleRenderer_text__GaXOv" data-testid="text-content">
 \n<div>\n<p>Get ready to dive into a world where art meets animal passion!
  Join the Evanston Animal Shelter for their The Love of Animals Art Show\,
  an awesome in-person event celebrating the beauty and charm of their furr
 y 4-legged friends. If you're an art and/or pet lover\, there's something 
 here that'll steal your heart. Including sweet dogs and cats ready for ado
 ption. Swing by\, soak up the creative vibes\, and maybe even find a piece
  that speaks to your soul. Free treats\, drinks &amp\; fun! <a href="https
 ://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-love-of-animals-art-show-benefiting-the-evanst
 on-animal-shelter-tickets-1980524597385?utm-campaign=social&amp\;utm-conte
 nt=attendeeshare&amp\;utm-medium=discovery&amp\;utm-term=listing&amp\;utm-
 source=cp&amp\;aff=ebdsshcopyurl" target="_blank">Visit their Eventbrite f
 or more info</a>.&nbsp\;</p>\n</div>\n</div>
LOCATION:Evanston Animal Shelter\, 2310 Oakton St.
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-love-of-animals-art-show-benefiting-t
 he-evanston-animal-shelter-tickets-1980524597385?utm-campaign=social&utm-c
 ontent=attendeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&a
 ff=ebdsshcopyurl
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sing a Better Future Into Existence
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T150000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:43beaa05c3a86c0016816843d4ad7146@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:Sing a Better Future Into Existence on Saturday\, March 14\, f
 rom 3 to 5 p.m. at <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inlin
 e cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Trinity L
 utheran Church</span></span>\, 3637 Golf Road\, Evanston. This participato
 ry &ldquo\;Singing Resistance&rdquo\; gathering is not a concert\, but an 
 afternoon of community singing rooted in courage\, solidarity\, and hope. 
 Open to all\, no musical experience needed. The event welcomes people of e
 very faith tradition and those with none. A donation is invited\, with pro
 ceeds supporting mutual aid networks in Minneapolis&ndash\;St. Paul. Seati
 ng\, elevator access\, a hearing loop\, and an all-gender restroom are ava
 ilable. <a href="https://www.tickettailor.com/events/commonpulse/2081933" 
 target="_blank">Register online in advance</a>.
LOCATION:Trinity Lutheran Church\, 3637 Golf Road
URL:https://www.tickettailor.com/events/commonpulse/2081933
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jamming Jean Concert featuring Street Jaxkson Band
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T170000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T190000
UID:3f5320579edf9373f04ae394f35b6871@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<div id="comp-mmfddhkm" class="ku3DBC zQ9jDz qvSjx3 Vq6kJx com
 p-mmfddhkm wixui-rich-text" data-testid="richTextElement">\n<p class="font
 _7 wixui-rich-text__text">Join the Levy Senior Foundation on Friday\, Marc
 h 20\, at 5 p.m.&nbsp\;for a&nbsp\;free&nbsp\;Jamming Jean concert featuri
 ng the Street Jaxkson Band\, one of Chicagoland&rsquo\;s hottest blues var
 iety bands.</p>\n</div>\n<div id="comp-mmfddhkv" class="ku3DBC zQ9jDz qvSj
 x3 Vq6kJx comp-mmfddhkv wixui-rich-text" data-testid="richTextElement">\n<
 p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text"
 >Blending blues with funk\, rock &rsquo\;n&rsquo\; roll\, R&amp\;B\, and r
 eggae\, this energetic five-piece group delivers a lively mix of classic f
 avorites and danceable hits that keep audiences engaged from start to fini
 sh. Known for their dynamic stage presence and crowd interaction\, the Str
 eet Jaxkson Band creates a fun\, feel-good atmosphere that gets people mov
 ing. Their high-energy performances and crowd-pleasing sound have made the
 m a favorite throughout the Chicagoland area.</span></p>\n<p class="font_8
  wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">This concert w
 ill be held&nbsp\;inside the Levy Senior Center Gym from 5 p.m. to 7 p.m.&
 nbsp\;Enjoy dinner from Hecky&rsquo\;s Barbeque\, along with drinks\, all 
 available for cash purchase.</span></p>\n<p class="font_8 wixui-rich-text_
 _text"><span class="wixui-rich-text__text">All ages are welcome to this fr
 ee\, family-friendly\, community event!&nbsp\;No registration is required 
 for this free concert.</span></p>\n</div>
LOCATION:Levy Senior Center
URL:https://www.lscfevanston.org/levy-music-series
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Levy Longevity: Strength Training for Anxiety with Shaun Zetlin
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T103000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T120000
UID:9dc0fd6e959c3ed4b338ff2c9d3565a2@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<h2 align="left"><strong>Levy Longevity: Strength Training for
  Anxiety with Shaun Zetlin</strong></h2>\n<p align="left">Feeling anxious 
 or overwhelmed is more common than many people realize\, especially during
  times of stress or life change. Join Shaun Zetlin online via Zoom on Tues
 day\, March 10\, at 1:30 p.m. for a senior-friendly program focused on how
  gentle strength training can support calmness\, confidence\, and emotiona
 l resilience. This program will include simple\, beginner-friendly exercis
 es that can be done standing or seated\, while also improving balance and 
 overall strength. Shaun will also share practical tools and key concepts f
 rom his book&nbsp\;<em>Emotional Fitness</em>&nbsp\;to help you feel stron
 ger both mentally and physically! This&nbsp\;virtual&nbsp\;program is&nbsp
 \;free to attend\, but&nbsp\;registration is required.&nbsp\;Visit&nbsp\;<
 a rel="noopener" href="https://links-1.govdelivery.com/CL0/http:%2F%2Flscf
 evanston.org%2F/1/0100019cd34d491f-37100db2-dc76-4f97-b291-98b5566238c1-00
 0000/_ktw0ZjfF8fAQ4nB8w4sLWXSh4YOq9bcfKGp4bWFREI=447" target="_blank" data
 -saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://links-1.govdelivery
 .com/CL0/http:%252F%252Flscfevanston.org%252F/1/0100019cd34d491f-37100db2-
 dc76-4f97-b291-98b5566238c1-000000/_ktw0ZjfF8fAQ4nB8w4sLWXSh4YOq9bcfKGp4bW
 FREI%3D447&amp\;source=gmail&amp\;ust=1773157991500000&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0GkG
 J-bdL9PgE8u7OpnTjR">lscfevanston.o<wbr />rg</a>&nbsp\;to register.</p>
LOCATION:Virtual
URL:https://www.lscfevanston.org/
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston
END:VEVENT
